% question 1
\begin{q}[10 points]

  A report on Facebook suggests that Facebook apps can
  generate large amounts of money, as much as \$1 million a
  month. The following table gives the numbers of Facebook
  users by country for the top 10 countries based on the
  number of users:
  \begin{center}
    \begin{tabular}{lcl}
      \textbf{Country} && \textbf{Users} \textbf{(in millions)} \\
      \hline
      Brazil && 29.30 \\
      India && 37.38 \\
      Mexico && 29.80 \\
      Germany && 21.46 \\
      France && 23.19 \\
      Philippines && 26.87 \\
      Indonesia && 40.52 \\
      United Kingdom && 30.39 \\
      United States && 155.74 \\
      Turkey && 30.36 \\
      \hline
    \end{tabular}
  \end{center}
  \begin{enumerate}
  \item Use a bar graph to describe the numbers of users in
    these countries.
  \item Do you think that the United States is an outlier in
    this data set? Explain your answer.
  \item Describe the major features of your graph in a short paragraph.
  \end{enumerate}
  
\end{q}


